     2→//! module_22 – Runtime-hot-swappable sentiment analysis strategies and Kafka
     3→//! stream processor used by ChirpPulse.
     4→//!
     5→//! This module demonstrates how data-scientists can plug-in new sentiment
     6→//! algorithms without taking the pipeline offline.  A registry keeps multiple
     7→//! strategies in memory and a lightweight control message on the
     8→//! `STRATEGY_CONTROL_TOPIC` lets operators promote a new default strategy
     9→//! instantly.  The processor consumes raw social messages, enriches them with
    10→//! sentiment, and republishes them to the lake in real-time.
    11→//!
    12→//! Production-ready aspects demonstrated here:
    13→//! • async Kafka consumer/producer (`rdkafka` + `tokio`)  
    14→//! • Strategy pattern with dynamic dispatch & hot-swap capabilities  
    15→//! • Robust error handling (`thiserror`) and observability (`tracing`)  
    16→//! • Graceful back-pressure and DLQ for poison messages  
    17→//!
    18→//! NOTE: In a real deployment this module would live in its own crate with the
    19→//! dependencies declared in `Cargo.toml`.  For brevity all source is presented
    20→//! in a single file.
